sql:
SELECT user_name, followers
FROM users
ORDER BY followers DESC;

SELECT user_id, MAX(engagement_score) AS max_engagement_score
FROM engagement_metrics
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT user_id
FROM (
    SELECT user_id, engagement_score, PERCENT_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY engagement_score DESC) AS engagement_rank
    FROM engagement_metrics
) ranked_users
WHERE engagement_rank <= 0.10;

SELECT log_date, activity_type
FROM activity_logs
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT engagement_id, user_id, engagement_score, engagement_date
FROM engagement_metrics
ORDER BY engagement_score DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "big city" refers to San Francisco, CA;
- "large crowd" means more than 12,000 followers;
- "official certification" implies the user is verified;
- "most engaging" means the user has the highest engagement score.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS active_user_count
FROM activity_logs
WHERE log_date >= DATE('now','-30 days');

SELECT AVG(followers) AS average_followers
FROM users
WHERE activity_level = 'High' AND user_is_verified = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "shining stars" metaphorically refers to the most engaged users;
- "captured the hearts of their followers" relates to having a high number of followers;
- "dazzled the social media with their engagement" metaphorically refers to high engagement scores;
- "brightest sparkle to their name" refers to the top 5 users with the highest engagement scores.
